@Xewiz2001 5. this was mentioned in the video - and "at least a few hours" is wrong. If you want to charge from ~10% to 80% that takes roughly 30-40 minutes in the quickest charging cars (Teslas). Some of the smaller and lower range cars can also charge up full in 15-20 minutes.
6. There are more places to charge electric cars than there are gas stations. Every electric outlet (i.e. the vast majority of buildings in the world) have at least one of these. But you're right that there's still less quick chargers. This is changing rapidly though. Take a look at plugshare's website.
7. "car guys" is a wide term. I used to love the noise of sports cars. I still do a bit for some of them, but now the sound often makes me think of sitting on the can and squeezing a hard one. In other words, desperate and stressful. And EVs are not entirely soundless. It sounds like a quiet jet engine when you step on it. To me, it sounds vigorous and "futuristic" (e.g. Dark Knight's batmobile has the same sound in stealth mode and other times). But most of all, I think it's actually also very enjoyable to hear the road (and elements) more clearly.  I think it's a good supplement to "feeling the road", as "car guys" often enjoy.

